[{"id":44407,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the fundamental frequency in a stretched string is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>For the first mass, it can be written that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And, for the second mass, it can be written that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (3) by equation (2) and simplify to obtain the required mass.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (4) to calculate the required mass.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>180</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></mstyle></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>500</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44546,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$2000 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}$","$5 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}$","$20 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}$","$5 \\pi \\mathrm{m} / \\mathrm{s}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\mathrm{v}=\\frac{\\omega}{\\mathrm{k}}=5 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":44386,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["5.0 cm","20 cm","10 cm","2.5 cm"],"answer":0,"solution":"Minimum distance between 2 points having same speed is $\\frac{\\lambda}{2}$.<br/>$\\lambda=\\frac{2 \\pi}{\\mathrm{k}}=\\frac{1}{10} \\mathrm{~m}=10 \\mathrm{~cm}$<br/>$\\text { Distance }=\\frac{\\lambda}{2}=5 \\mathrm{~cm}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44445,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>81</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>169</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Data provided in the question is, the ratio of the intensities,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo></math></p><p>After taking square root of above equation on both sides, we get,</p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Apply componendo and dividendo,<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></mrow><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></mrow><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>min</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44406,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The fundamental frequency is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math>.</p><p>The length of the&nbsp;string is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Linear mass density is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>l</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Using&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>18</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (15 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44380,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["3","4","1","2"],"answer":3,"solution":"Fifth harmonic of closed organ pipe equals first harmonic of open pipe:<br>$f_{5\\text{ closed}} = f_{1\\text{ open}}$<br>$\\frac{5v}{4L_{\\text{closed}}} = \\frac{v}{2L_{\\text{open}}}$<br>$\\frac{L_{\\text{closed}}}{L_{\\text{open}}} = \\frac{5}{2}$<br>Since the ratio is $\\frac{5}{x}$, we get $x = 2$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44405,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The formula to calculate the fundamental frequency in a closed pipe is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And, that in an open pipe is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Given that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>o</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From equations (1), (2) and (3), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>150</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>350</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>600</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>700</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>m</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>42</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>42</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>7</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>294</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44490,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math><mn>12</mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math><mn>15</mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math><mn>4</mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math><mn>11</mn><mo>°</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Asin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>1000</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>)</mo></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#969;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1000</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math><br />at temperature&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>,</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>336</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>1000</mn><mn>336</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>273</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>277</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>41</mn><mtext>K</mtext></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44378,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$|f_A - f_B| = 4$<br>$|f_A - 380| = 4$<br>So, $f_A = 384$ Hz or $376$ Hz<br>on loading with wax $f_A$ decreases<br>So, $f_A = 384$ Hz","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44471,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>91</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>kmh</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>81</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>kmh</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>61</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>kmh</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>71</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>kmh</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Frequency appeared at wall</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>f</mtext><mtext>w</mtext></msub><mtext>=</mtext><mfrac><mtext>330</mtext><mtext>330-v</mtext></mfrac><mtext>.f&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</mtext><mo>.</mo><mo>.....</mo><mtext>(1)</mtext></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow><mn>330</mn></mfrac><mo>&#183;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>490</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#183;</mo><mn>420</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>330</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow><mn>91</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>38</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>91</mn><mi>Km</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44383,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Point B will $10^{\\text {th }}$ maxima<br>$\\Delta x=L_2 B-L_1 B$<br>$L_1 B=\\sqrt{20^2+40^2}=20 \\sqrt{5} \\mathrm{~m}=44.6 \\mathrm{~m}$<br>$L_2 B=\\sqrt{40^2+30^2}=50 \\mathrm{~m}$<br>$\\Delta x=50-44.6=5.4 \\mathrm{~m}$<br>$\\Delta x=n \\lambda$<br>$5.4=10 \\times \\lambda$<br>$\\lambda=0.54 \\mathrm{~m}$<br>$V=f \\lambda$<br>$f=\\frac{324}{0.54}=600 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44478,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p><math><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#961;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#961;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#961;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>p</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>300</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>105.75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>&#8201;</mo><mo>&#8201;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8201;</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>1.41</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>106.05</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>&#8201;</mo><mo>&#8201;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>&#8201;</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>1.414</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (08 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44397,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"For closed organ pipe\n$\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}=(2 \\mathrm{n}+1) \\frac{\\mathrm{v}}{4 \\ell}=\\frac{15 \\mathrm{v}}{4 \\ell}$\nFor open organ pipe\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{o}}=(\\mathrm{n}+1) \\frac{\\mathrm{v}}{2 \\ell}=\\frac{8 \\mathrm{v}}{2 \\ell} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}}{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{o}}}=\\frac{15}{16}=\\frac{\\mathrm{a}-1}{\\mathrm{a}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{a}=16\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44547,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$300$","$600$","$1200$","$200$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$y=10^{-4} \\sin \\left(600 t-2 x+\\frac{\\pi}{3}\\right)$. Comparing it with standard equation\n$y=A \\sin (v t-k x) ; \\quad v=600 m / s$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":44506,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>3</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;be the number of antinodes of both wires.</p><p>Fundamental frequency remains the same for both wires.&nbsp;<br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>same</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>same</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>same</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>&#160;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>&#961;</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>From the above equation, we have&nbsp;<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msqrt><msub><mi>&#961;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msqrt><msub><mi>&#961;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi></msqrt></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>p</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>&#961;</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>&#961;</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><br />The ratio of antinodes is&nbsp;<math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (08 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":44538,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$18>x$","$x>54$","$54>x>36$","$36>x>18$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& n=\\frac{1}{4 x} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma R T}{M}} \\\\\n& x n=\\frac{1}{4} \\sqrt{\\frac{\\gamma R T}{M}} \\\\\n& x \\propto \\sqrt{T}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null},{"id":44536,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$49 \\mathrm{~m}$","$98 \\mathrm{~m}$","$147 \\mathrm{~m}$","$196 \\mathrm{~m}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Motor cycle, $u=0, a=2 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$\nObserver is in motion and source is at rest.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\Rightarrow n^{\\prime}=n \\frac{v-v_O}{v+v_S} \\Rightarrow \\frac{94}{100} n=n \\frac{330-v_O}{330} \\Rightarrow 330-v_0=\\frac{330 \\times 94}{100} \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow v_O=330-\\frac{94 \\times 33}{10}=\\frac{33 \\times 6}{10} \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s} \\\\\n& s=\\frac{v^2-u^2}{2 a}=\\frac{9 \\times 33 \\times 33}{100}=\\frac{9 \\times 1089}{100} \\approx 98 \\mathrm{~m} .\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":44449,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>For closed organ pipe</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>for minimum length, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>340</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>250</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>34</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44411,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The equation of the wave is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>160</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>The velocity of a wave is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p><p>A wave equation is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#981;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Using equation (i),</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>160</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.5</mo></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>320</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mrow/></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>320</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>18</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1152</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (11 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44448,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#8467;</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>550</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>11</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math><br />Thus, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math><br />Thus,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#8467;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>nv</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>500</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>900</mn><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44476,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math><mn>5.8</mn><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mn>0.2</mn><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><mn>3</mn><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a1da21a2-a133-4efd-98a4-512a3fb62d69.jpeg\" /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>R</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>A</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mi>R</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5.8</mn><mi></mi><msub><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi></mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44544,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$200 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$202 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$196 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$204 \\mathrm{~Hz}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$$\n\\left|f_1-f_2\\right|=4\n$$\nSince mass of second tuning fork increases so $f_2$ decrease and beats increase so\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& f_1>f_2 \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow f_2=f_1-4=196\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":44453,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The formula of apparent frequency in terms of velocity of the source and observer is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8242;</mi></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>s</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math>, now put the values which are given in the question,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1800</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>340</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>340</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1800</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>360</mn></mrow><mn>320</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2025</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44436,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>As we know particle velocity,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mfenced><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>n</mi></math></p><p>Now as we know,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>n</mi></math></p><p>As given in the question,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mfenced><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>v</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>20</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>n</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44431,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#960;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The given equation is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>The maximum particle velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>&#969;</mi></math></p><p>And the wave velocity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>For wave velocity to be equal to maximum particle&nbsp;velocity</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>&#969;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44530,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$a \\cos (k x-\\omega t+\\pi)$","$a \\cos (k x+\\omega t+\\pi)$","$a \\cos \\left(k x+\\omega t+\\frac{\\pi}{2}\\right)$","$a \\cos \\left(k x-\\omega t+\\frac{\\pi}{2}\\right)$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Since the point $x=0$ is a node and reflection is taking place from point $x=0$. This means that reflection must be taking place from the fixed end and hence the reflected ray must suffer an additional phase change of $\\pi$ or a path change of $\\frac{\\lambda}{2}$.\nSo, if $y_{\\text {incident }}=a \\cos (k x-\\omega t)$\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\Rightarrow y_{\\text {incident }} & =a \\cos (-k x-\\omega t+\\pi) \\\\\n& =-a \\cos (\\omega t+k x)\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nHence equation for the other wave\n$$\ny=a \\cos (k x+\\omega t+\\pi)\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":44520,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$\\frac{3 \\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{s}$","$\\frac{5 \\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{s}$","$\\frac{\\pi}{2} \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{s}$","$2 ~\\pi \\mathrm{~cm} / \\mathrm{s}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":44551,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["286 cps","292 cps","294 cps","288 cps"],"answer":1,"solution":"The fact that placing wax decreases the frequency of the unknown fork and also the beat frequency states that the unknown fork is of higher frequency.\n$$\nn-288=4 \\Rightarrow n=292 \\mathrm{cps}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":44412,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The general equation for a wave can be written as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>. Comparing it with the given equation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>003</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>rad</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>003</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Using the equation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>k</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>003</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44516,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Waves and Sound","question":"","options":["$2150 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$2500 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$1800 \\mathrm{~Hz}$","$2400 \\mathrm{~Hz}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Given $\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}=1800 \\mathrm{~Hz}$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}=\\mathrm{v} \\\\\n&\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{B}}=2150 \\mathrm{~Hz}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nReflected wave frequency received by $\\mathrm{A}$, $\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}{ }^{\\prime}=$ ?\nApplying doppler's effect of sound, $\\mathrm{f}^{\\prime}=\\frac{\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{s}} \\mathrm{f}}{\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{s}}-\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}}$\nHere, $\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}=\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{s}}\\left(1-\\frac{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}}{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{B}}}\\right)=343\\left(1-\\frac{1800}{2150}\\right)$ $\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}=55.8372 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}$\nNow, for the reflected wave,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\therefore \\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}{ }^{\\prime}=\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{s}}+\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}}{\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{s}}-\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{t}}}\\right) \\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}} \\\\\n&=\\left(\\frac{343+55.83}{343-55.83}\\right) \\times 1800 \\\\\n&=2499.44 \\approx 2500 \\mathrm{~Hz}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (12 Apr Online)","image":null}]